{{italic title}} {{main|Claude Monet}}
'''[[Claude Monet]]''' painted a [[Serial imagery|series]] of oil paintings of the [[Palace of Westminster]], home of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|British Parliament]], in the fall of 1899 and the early months of 1900 and 1901 during stays in London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/works-of-art/56.135.6|title=''Claude Monet: The Houses of Parliament (Effect of Fog)'' (56.135.6) In Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History. New York: The Metropolitan Museum of Art, 2000–. (December 2010)}}</ref> All of the series' paintings share the same viewpoint from Monet's window or a terrace at [[St Thomas' Hospital]] overlooking the [[Thames]] and the approximate canvas size of 81&nbsp;cm × 92&nbsp;cm (32 in × 36 3/8 in).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibiblio.org/wm/paint/auth/monet/parliament/|title=Monet, Claude: Houses of Parliament, London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2006/aug/09/science.arts|title='Hospital view. Experts decipher where Monet was standing', James Randerson, Wednesday 9 August 2006, Guardian Unlimited}}</ref> They are, however, painted during different times of the day and weather conditions.
By the time of the ''Houses of Parliament'' series, Monet had abandoned his earlier practice of completing a painting on the spot in front of the motif. He carried on refining the images back in France and sent to London for photographs to help in this. This caused some adverse reaction, but Monet's reply was that his means of creating a work was his own business and it was up to the viewer to judge the final result.
== Gallery == Some of the 19 known paintings in the ''Houses of Parliament'' series:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/life-and-style/homes-and-property/fine-art-antiques/monet-s-view-of-london-parliament-for-auction-1.2196572|title='Monet’s view of London parliament for auction', Michael Parsons, 2 May 2015, The Irish Times}}</ref> <gallery widths="200px" heights="200px" perrow="4"> File:Claude Monet, Houses of Parliament, London, 1900-1903, 1933.1164, Art Institute of Chicago.jpg|''Houses of Parliament, London,'' 1900–1901 The [[Art Institute of Chicago]] Image:Monet Houses of Parliament, Sunset.jpg|''Parlement, coucher du soleil'' (sunset), 1902, private collection Image:Brouillard, London Parliament, Claude Monet.jpg|''Le Parlement, Effet de Brouillard'', 1903, [[Museum of Fine Arts (St. Petersburg, Florida)]] File:Houses of Parliament in the Fog by Claude Monet, High Museum of Art.jpg|''Houses of Parliament in the Fog'', 1903, [[High Museum of Art]] File:Monet, Claude, Houses of Parliament, Seagulls.jpg|''The Houses of Parliament, Seagulls'', 1903, [[Princeton University Art Museum]] Image:Westminster Parlement.jpg|''Le Parlement de Londres, soleil couchant'', 1903, [[National Gallery of Art]] [[Washington, DC.]] File:Claude Monet - The Houses of Parliament, Sunset.jpg|''The Houses of Parliament, Sunset'', 1903, [[National Gallery of Art]] [[Washington, DC.]] File:Brooklyn Museum - Houses of Parliament Sunlight Effect (Le Parlement effet de soleil) - Claude Monet.jpg|''Houses of Parliament Sunlight Effect (Le Parlement effet de soleil),'' 1903, [[Brooklyn Museum]] File:The Houses of Parliament (Effect of Fog).JPG|''The Houses of Parliament (Effect of Fog)'', 1903–1904, [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] Image:Claude Monet 015.jpg|''Trouée de soleil dans le brouillard'', Houses of Parliament, London, Sun Breaking Through the Fog, 1904, [[Musée d'Orsay]], [[Paris]] Image:Le Parlement de Londres Monet.jpg|''Houses of Parliament, stormy sky'', 1904, [[Palais des Beaux-Arts de Lille]], [[Lille, France]] File:Claude Monet - Le Parlement, coucher de soleil.jpg|''Houses of Parliament, London,'' ca. 1904, [[Kunsthaus Zürich]] File:Monet - Parlament in London - Stürmischer Tag.jpg|''Parliament in London – Stormy day'', ca. 1904 File:Seagulls, the Thames & Houses of Parliament by Claude Monet, Pushkin Museum.JPG|''Seagulls, the River Thames and the Houses of Parliament'', 1904, [[Pushkin Museum]] File:Claude Monet, Londres, Le Parlement, Reflets sur la Tamise, 1905, huile sur toile, Musée Marmottan Monet, Paris.jpg|''Houses of Parliament, London,'' [[Musée Marmottan Monet]], 1905 File:Westminster palace.jpg|Photograph of the Palace of Westminster from [[London Eye]] </gallery>
==Public display==
In 2018, the [[Tate Britain]] in [[Central London|London]] exhibited six paintings of the series, together in a single room, for the duration of a temporary exhibition titled ''Impressionists in London, French artists in exile (1870-1904)'', devoted to the temporary exile of French and [[impressionist]] artists in London during the [[Franco-Prussian War]]. This was a rare occurrence because no museum owns or exhibits more than two in a permanent collection.<ref>{{cite news | last=Brown | first=Mark | url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2017/jul/18/monet-uk-parliament-paintings-feature-impressionism-tate-britain-exhibition | title=Monet's UK parliament paintings to feature in Tate Britain exhibition | website=The Guardian | date=18 July 2017 | accessdate=26 March 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last=Sooke | first=Alastair | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/art/what-to-see/not-impressionistic-beautiful-impressionists-londontate-britain/ | title=Not very impressionistic, but beautiful all the same - Impressionists in London Tate Britain, review | website=The Telegraph | date=30 October 2017 | accessdate=26 March 2018 }}</ref>
The paintings were also shown at the [[Petit Palais]] when the temporary exhibition travelled from London to [[Paris]].<ref>{{cite news | last=Palais | first=Petit | url=http://www.petitpalais.paris.fr/en/expositions/impressionists-london | title=Impressionists in London | website=Petit Palais | date=1 January 2018 | accessdate=25 May 2018 }}</ref>
The six paintings were the examples from the following collections:
* [[Art Institute of Chicago]] * [[Brooklyn Museum]] * Kaiser Wilhelm Museum<ref>{{cite news | last=Krefeld | first=Kuntsmuseen | url=http://www.kunstmuseenkrefeld.de/e/sammlung/kunstvor1945/index.html | title=Art Before 1945 | website=Kunstmuseen Krefeld | date=1 January 2018 | accessdate=3 April 2018 }}</ref> * [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] * [[Musée d'Orsay]] * [[Museum of modern art André Malraux - MuMa]]
