{{For|the EU legislative mechanism|Formal Trilogue meeting}}

A trilogue is a literary form in which an imagined conversation between three participants is recorded. Extant examples<ref>{{cite book|last1=Davy|first1=Humphrey|title=Consolations in Travel|date=1830|publisher=John Murray|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Ramsden|first1=Jeremy|title=Chemicals all around us|date=2015|publisher=In: Ampthill Literary Festival Yearbook|isbn=978-1-5175506-8-4|pages=29–38}}</ref> suggest that it is used especially to treat scientific, especially chemical and philosophical, topics.

